@startuml
' Rendered to connection-states.svg by .github/workflows/plantuml.yml
' (docs/ABC.puml → docs/ABC.svg). Keep @startuml bare: a named @startuml
' would override the output filename and break that convention. To preview
' locally, run `make diagrams` (same pinned renderer as CI; see
' PLANTUML_IMAGE in the Makefile).
'
' Source of truth: the behavior dispatch in
' internal/actor/connection/connection.go (Receive, preAuthBehavior,
' postAuthBehavior, newClosingBehavior).

state "Pre-auth" as pre : awaits an auth frame\ncarrying the JWT
state "Post-auth" as post : writes room events and\nheartbeats to the socket
state "Closing" as closing : close frame queued;\ndrops everything else

[*] -down-> pre : Started: pumps and heartbeat start,\nauth deadline scheduled
pre -down-> post : auth accepted;\nPID registered\nwith the User grain
pre -down-> closing : auth rejected, auth timeout,\nprotocol violation, pong timeout
post -down-> closing : pong timeout
closing -down-> [*] : write pump flushes the close\nframe, then the actor stops

note left of post
  From every phase, transport tear-down
  (peer close, pump failure) stops the
  actor directly. Once auth has registered
  the PID, the User grain's watch observes
  the termination and evicts the connection.
end note
@enduml
